                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>30</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2 Inches</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>36</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2-1/4 Inches</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the pawl assembly and tighten the capscrew to 15-20 ft-lbs. (20-27 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">On vehicles with the "pull" pawl button design, remove the screwdriver.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The "pull" button pawl design assembly is interchangeable with the older design as a complete
                        assembly only.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>The tamper resistant spring brake has been factory sealed for your protection. There are no
                        user serviceable parts inside the spring brake chamber. If you experience any damage or failure
                        to the spring brake chamber, replace the complete assembly. Never attempt to disas- semble the
                        spring brake chamber as serious personal injury or death could result from accidental sudden
                        release of the high energy spring.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the axle has a spring (PARKING) brake chamber, release CAGED spring. Refer to GROUP 04 -
                BRAKES in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Test vehicle for correct brake operation before putting vehicle back into service.</para>
        </step1>
